==English==

===Noun===
'''"Noob"''' A noob is a 'newbie" that that thinks he already knows how to do
everything. "Newbies" know that they are new and inexperinced however a "noob" 
believes that he knows everything. "noobs" are often found backmouthing veterans,
and usualy never get anywhere.

'''noob'''
# (''internet'') (''derogatory'') a [[newbie]]
#: ''Noobs are annoying, they never know the [[forum]] rules.''
# (''gaming'') (''derogatory'') someone who plays at a beginner level
#: ''You just got [[pwnted]], noob.''
#: "Noobs liek it from behined."

